title: Report online material promoting terrorism or extremism

heading_context: Report online material promoting terrorism or extremism
chunks.html_content:
Report illegal or harmful information, pictures or videos you’ve found on the internet.

You can report things like:

  • articles, images, speeches or videos that promote terrorism or encourage violence
  • websites made by terrorist or extremist organisations
  • videos of terrorist attacks
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Report online material promoting terrorism or extremism
chunks.html_content: You can make your report without leaving your name and contact details.

heading_context: Report online material promoting terrorism or extremism
chunks.html_content: Call 999 if you are reporting a crime that is in progress or if someone is in immediate danger.
chunks.plain_content:
Report online material promoting terrorism or extremism

heading_context: Report online material promoting terrorism or extremism
chunks.html_content:
You do not have to provide evidence. However it can help an investigation if you include:

  • screenshots
  • links to the website or platform (for example an app)
